# Action Tracker and Context Rule

Whenever you start a new conversation or session, your VERY FIRST action should be to read the `docs/action_tracker.md` file — especially the **"Session Handoff"** section at the top if present (current pickup point for in-progress work).

This file acts as the central source of truth for the project, tracking:
- Completed work
- Ongoing bugs
- High, Medium, and Low priority backlog items
- Architectural decisions

By reading this file, you will seamlessly pick up the context from previous conversations and avoid losing progress.